                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 11.393,
                                "byte_start": 86853,
                                "byte_stop": 132515,
                                "text": "The opinion the court in number 94-3, Reynoldsville Casket Company v. Hyde will be announced by Justice Breyer."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 11.393,
                        "stop": 140.957,
                        "byte_start": 132515,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15139,
                            "name": "Stephen G. Breyer",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/stephen_g_breyer",
                            "last_name": "Breyer",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2785,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 775890000,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Bill Clinton",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2785"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32682,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 49908,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/stephen_g_breyer_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 7777,
                            "identifier": "stephen_g_breyer"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 11.393,
                                "stop": 16.059,
                                "byte_start": 132515,
                                "byte_stop": 151114,
                                "text": "Mrs. Hyde is the respondent in this case she is from Ohio."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 16.059,
                                "stop": 23.041,
                                "byte_start": 151114,
                                "byte_stop": 179117,
                                "text": "She was in an automobile accident which involved the truck owned by a Pennsylvania company, it\u2019s called Reynoldsville Casket."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 23.041,
                                "stop": 34.173,
                                "byte_start": 179117,
                                "byte_stop": 223630,
                                "text": "She sued the company in Ohio more than three years after the accident and normally that would have been too late because the Ohio statute it is only two years."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 34.173,
                                "stop": 51.884,
                                "byte_start": 223630,
                                "byte_stop": 294474,
                                "text": "But there was a special tolling provision in the Ohio Law which gave her more time to sue a company because it was out of state and while her suit was pending this court in a case called Bendix held that tolling provision was unconstitutional."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 51.884,
                                "stop": 55.743,
                                "byte_start": 294474,
                                "byte_stop": 309834,
                                "text": "So Reynoldsville immediately came in and said you have to dismiss your suit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 55.743,
                                "stop": 61.073,
                                "byte_start": 309834,
                                "byte_stop": 331150,
                                "text": "The Supreme Court in a different case held that this tolling provision is unconstitutional."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 61.073,
                                "stop": 86.863,
                                "byte_start": 331150,
                                "byte_stop": 434386,
                                "text": "While the Supreme Court of Ohio said, we don\u2019t have to dismiss the suit because we\u2019re not going to apply this Law to the people whose cases were pending at that time and we had to decide if they could do that and basically this court has held that if a new rule of constitutional law applies to the case in which the court announces it, it also applies to all pending cases."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 86.863,
                                "stop": 113.905,
                                "byte_start": 434386,
                                "byte_stop": 542533,
                                "text": "That would seem to require a judgment for Reynoldsville and Mrs. Hyde argued rather complicated argument that really what was going on as they were applying the rule backwards but they just didn\u2019t give Reynoldsville a remedy, and we in our opinion say well we don\u2019t really see that as a distinction and we go through the various cases that she sights in support and we distinguish them and we ultimately come to the conclusion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 113.905,
                                "stop": 127.97,
                                "byte_start": 542533,
                                "byte_stop": 598749,
                                "text": "It\u2019s not a distinction that Ohio has to apply our new rule retroactively, that Ohio has to apply the rule to her case and therefore Reynoldsville is entitled to judgment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 127.97,
                                "stop": 140.957,
                                "byte_start": 598749,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "There is in fact as well Justice Scalia filed a concurring opinion in which Justice Thomas joins and Justice Kennedy has filed an opinion concurring in the judgment in which Justice O\u2019Connor joins."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
